      <h1 class='title'>Darwin Initiative</h1>
    </div>
    <div class='commons-written-statements-sitting' id='content'>
      
      <cite class='section'>HC Deb 15 July 2003 vol 409 cc11-2WS</cite>
      <a class='permalink column-permalink' id='column_11ws' title='Col. 11WS &mdash; HC Deb 15 July 2003 vol 409 c11WS' name='column_11ws' href='#column_11ws' rel='bookmark'>11WS</a>
      <div class='hentry member_contribution' id='S6CV0409P0-02290'>
        <a name='S6CV0409P0_20030715_CWS_3'>  </a>
        <blockquote cite='http://hansard.millbanksystems.com/people/mr-elliot-morley' class='contribution_text entry-content'>
          <a class='speech-permalink permalink' href='#S6CV0409P0_20030715_CWS_3' title='Link to this speech by Mr Elliot Morley' rel='bookmark'>&sect;</a>
          <cite class='member author entry-title'><a href="/people/mr-elliot-morley" title="Mr Elliot Morley">The Minister for the Environment (Mr. Elliot Morley)</a></cite>
          <p class="first-para" id="S6CV0409P0-02290">I am pleased to announce to the House awards under a new funding scheme forming part of DEFRA's Darwin Initiative.</p><p id="S6CV0409P0-02291">The Darwin Initiative is an annual small grants programme which uses UK expertise working with local partners to help countries rich in biodiversity but poor in resources to conserve and use their biodiversity sustainably. Launched at the Rio summit in 1992, the initiative has committed more than &#x00A3;30 million to over 300 projects in around 100 countries. More than 100 projects are currently running. The Prime Minister announced an increase in the Darwin Initiative budget in his speech on WSSD in September. The budget increased from &#x00A3;3 million to &#x00A3;4 million in 2003&#x2013;04 and will rise to &#x00A3;5 million in 2004&#x2013;05, and &#x00A3;7 million a year from 2005&#x2013;06. Three new Darwin Initiative schemes have been launched as part of Phase II of the Initiative: Darwin Initiative scholarships, pre-project awards and post-project funding. Together these will help to help embed the core aims of capacity building, partnership and legacy. I announced the Scholarship awards at the annual Darwin lecture on 21 May.</p><a class='permalink column-permalink' id='column_12ws' title='Col. 12WS &mdash; HC Deb 15 July 2003 vol 409 c12WS' name='column_12ws' href='#column_12ws' rel='bookmark'>12WS</a><p id="S6CV0409P0-02292">The awards of pre-project funding are as follows: (Annex B)</p><p id="S6CV0409P0-02293">
          <table>
          <tr>
          <td><span class="italic">Organisation</span></td>
          <td><span class="italic">Project Title</span></td>
